summary: i’ve been scrolling through the fandom, and it really shocks me to see the hate that dany has? i don’t understand? this woman...
body:
i’ve been scrolling through the fandom, and it really shocks me to see the hate that dany has?

i don’t understand? this woman stood for everything good and because she had a moment where she fell, she’s condemned entirely for it? all the good she’s done was just tossed out the window. one bad move ( yes, okay it was a big move, i can’t disagree there ) but suddenly she’s a villain! people have done a lot of awful things in this show. she isn’t perfect, but no one is damn near that. i’m not saying it’s okay to put a city to ruins, but at least be understanding of where it came from. she lost it. kindness and mercy.. to have those used against you as weak points? that’s a different kind cruelty. those are virtues of a good leader, of a noble human. but those traits were pitted against her and at that point, i feel like she just lost her shit. to see your most trusted friend, advisor, maiden, just.. the person who’s been by your side the majority of your journey, get ruthlessly beheaded? and literally just prior, she had just lost another one of her children. and don’t forget the stress of finding out the truth about the man she loved. one thing after another. even - i -lost it for her.

she is human. she is flawed. we all are. doesn’t that make her character much more interesting? if not relatable, at least?

this woman moved through fire with fire in her HEART to do the right thing, to claim all she had left to her, and it backlashed. terribly. all she ever dreamed, the stories and tales she’s been told…. all she’d ever known, was so close to her grasp. so close, she touched it. and then it was over. 

i never thought i’d feel for a character in a way such as this in this series. i think everyone is great in the show and has something to offer, really - there are so many likable characters. but dany tugs on my heart. she took the cake.

&& she deserved the iron throne.

summary: I have this headcanon where Ned, Rhaegar, and Lyanna were hardcore rooting for Jon and Daenerys to restore House Targaryen in...
body:
I have this headcanon where Ned, Rhaegar, and Lyanna were hardcore rooting for Jon and Daenerys to restore House Targaryen in the afterlife. Then when Daenerys shows up they shower her with love and affection. Rhaegar is super proud of her.

Robb & Talisa and Rickon treat her like the sister she wanted to be to Arya, Sansa, and Bran. The fallen direwolves love her- even Lady.

Dany gets to meet her mother and Rhaego for the first time. Rhaella hugs and comforts her; she is so proud of Dany and says that nothing was her fault. Rhaego watched Dany every day and waited patiently for her. He finally gets to be in his Mommy’s arms.

Daenerys gets to be with Missandei, Jorah, Ser Barristan, Viserion, Rhaegal, Drogo, and Irri again.

Dany doesn’t hurt anymore. She is finally home.

…

Years later, after Jon lead a miserable, guilty, and unfulfilling existence, he shows up. Rhaegar and Lyanna had once expected to meet the king to Daenerys I, now they are just disappointed. Rhaegar doesn’t want anything to do with him for a time, not after what he did to Dany. Rhaegal never lands near him.

Ned doesn’t say anything, but Jon knows that he is also disappointed in him. It hurts.

Robb and Rickon are happier to see him, but they quickly give him the cold shoulder.

Jon always stares longingly at Dany’s house, the biggest one with a red door and a lemon tree. It’s the place where everyone hangs out; where they love and worship her. He has been warned to stay away.

When he finally gets the chance to apologize. She doesn’t say much and goes back to being surrounded by her loving family, while he is left outside indefinitely.

I might turn this into a fanfic if I can hold back my tears long enough to write it.

summary: asoiaf meme ♕ [2/5] scenes » The birth of dragons And after them came her handmaids, and then the others, all the Dothraki, men...
caption:
asoiaf meme ♕ [2/5] scenes » The birth of dragons

And after them came her handmaids, and then the others, all the Dothraki, men and women and children, and Dany had only to look at their eyes to know that they were hers now, today and tomorrow and forever, hers as they had never been Drogo’s.
As Daenerys Targaryen rose to her feet, her black hissed, pale smoke venting from its mouth and nostrils. The other two pulled away from her breasts and added their voices to the call, translucent wings unfolding and stirring the air, and for the first time in hundreds of years, the night came alive with the music of dragons.

summary: I find interesting one thing in ADWD, Jon has the opportunity to become a legal Stark, to be Lord of Winterfell and take Val as...
question: I find interesting one thing in ADWD, Jon has the opportunity to become a legal Stark, to be Lord of Winterfell and take Val as his wife, but he refuse. Dany has the option to marry to keep peace in Meereen, marry someone she doesn't love to avoid a war and she does. Both characters do what it's best for others and with doing this, they are rejecting happiness for themselves. It's sad how young they are and how many responsabilities they are taking, their ending it's not fair
answer:
There’s still no ending to call unfair, anon! This bears repeating: the story hasn’t ended yet. Believe me, as someone who oscillates between despair and hope, I still end up choosing the side of optimism, in which Jon and Dany will end up finding that angle of repose, so to speak, where they act their duty through love, and not at the expense of it. And it’s all because at the end of the day, Martin’s words still have enough goodness in them to make me choose that side of the fence.

Heroes are meant to suffer by design, and their story is worthy of being told because they happen to not be ordinary. Of course, they have to let go of their own happiness for something much bigger than themselves at some point; let’s just hope against all odds that their happiness will someday align with what they think is best for the others.
